properties.sfomuseum:description: Airmail flight cover, part of International Tributes to the History of Flight series by the Postal Commemorative Society; white envelope with full color illustration cachet and inset stamp commemorating first regular U.S. airmail service on May 15, 1918, at Bustleton Station, Pennsylvania, U.S.A., by Lieutenant Torrey Webb, U.S. Army, with Curtiss Jenny biplane; cancellation stamp dated May 15, 1984 in Philadelphia; includes information on reverse.
